subject: p11893091
Findings: Compared to the study from the prior day, the dual-lead pacemaker is unchanged. There is increased cardiomegaly, which is moderate-to-severe. Bilateral hazy vasculature, pulmonary vascular redistribution, and alveolar edema. There are small bilateral effusions, right greater than left and Kerley B lines. Compared to the prior exam, the CHF is worsened.
